## Advanced Usage

### Using Behind a Proxy
```bash
export HTTPS_PROXY="http://127.0.0.1:12345"
export HTTP_PROXY="http://127.0.0.1:12345"
firebase deploy
```

---

### Using as a Node Module

```javascript
const client = require("firebase-tools");

// List Android apps in project "foo"
client.apps
  .list("ANDROID", { project: "foo" })
  .then((data) => {
    console.log(data);
  })
  .catch((err) => {
    console.error(err);
  });

// Equivalent to: firebase --project="foo" apps:list ANDROID
```

**Note:** Positional arguments come first, options object last. All commands return Promises.

---

## Common Workflows

### Initial Setup
```bash
firebase login
firebase init
firebase serve
```

### Development with Emulators
```bash
firebase emulators:start
firebase emulators:exec "npm test"
```

### Deploy to Production
```bash
firebase deploy
firebase deploy --only functions  # Deploy only Cloud Functions
firebase deploy --only hosting    # Deploy only Hosting
```

